<eesti> 3.2.2. </eesti>
<inglise> Monitoring of conformity </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;uetele vastavuse j&auml;lgimine </eesti>
<inglise> If necessary, monitoring is carried out of the conformity of intermediate states of the product and at the main stages of its production. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;uetele vastavust j&auml;lgitakse vajaduse korral toote vahestaadiumides ja tootmisprotsessi p&otilde;hietappides. </eesti>
<inglise> This monitoring of conformity focuses where necessary on the product throughout the process of manufacture, so that only products having passed the scheduled intermediate controls and tests are dispatched. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;uetele vastavuse j&auml;lgimisel keskendutakse tootele vajaduse korral kogu tootmisprotsessi v&auml;ltel, nii et edasi saadetakse ainult sellised tooted, mis on l&auml;binud etten&auml;htud vahekontrollid ja -katsed. </eesti>
<inglise> 3.2.3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3.2.3. </eesti>
<inglise> Tests </inglise>
<eesti> Katsed </eesti>
<inglise> Tests should be in accordance with the test plan and be carried out in accordance with the methods indicated in the technical specification. </inglise>
<eesti> Katseid tehakse vastavalt katsekavale ja tehnilises kirjelduses osutatud meetoditele. </eesti>
<inglise> These methods should generally be direct methods. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud meetodid peaksid &uuml;ldjuhul olema otsesed. </eesti>
<inglise> It is however possible, in the case of certain characteristics, that the prescribed specification gives the possibility of using indirect test methods if a definite correlation or relationship can be established and if possible verified between specified characteristic X - the characteristic to be verified - and another characteristic Y which is easier or safer to measure than characteristic X. Indirect test methods may be retained when available and appropriate. </inglise>
<eesti> Teatavate omaduste puhul on siiski v&otilde;imalik, et etten&auml;htud kirjelduses lubatakse kasutada kaudseid katsemeetodeid juhul, kui saab teha kindlaks kontrollitava omaduse X kindla seose omadusega Y, mida m&otilde;&otilde;ta on lihtsam v&otilde;i ohutum kui omadust X, ja seda seost t&otilde;endada. Vajaduse ja v&otilde;imaluse korral v&otilde;ib kaudsete katsemeetodite kasutamist j&auml;tkata. </eesti>
<inglise> Depending on the system of attestation of conformity adopted for the product or the product family, initial type tests on the product may be carried out by the manufacturer himself or must be carried out or validated by an approved body. </inglise>
<eesti> Olenevalt toote v&otilde;i tootepere puhul kasutusele v&otilde;etud vastavuse t&otilde;endamise s&uuml;steemist v&otilde;ib toote esmased t&uuml;&uuml;bikatsetused teha tootja ise v&otilde;i peab need tegema v&otilde;i kinnitama volitatud asutus. </eesti>
<inglise> In the latter case, this obligation only applies to tests to determine characteristics for which the choice of attestation of conformity system requires the intervention of an approved body or laboratory. </inglise>
<eesti> Viimane kohustus kehtib ainult selliste omaduste kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramiseks tehtavate katsete kohta, mille jaoks valitud vastavuse t&otilde;endamise s&uuml;steemis n&otilde;utakse volitatud asutuse v&otilde;i labori osalemist. </eesti>
<inglise> These characteristics are given in Annex 3 of the mandates. </inglise>
<eesti> Need omadused on esitatud mandaatide 3. lisas. </eesti>
<inglise> The same is true for audit tests on samples taken from the factory, market or site when the system of attestation of conformity adopted is the certification of the product and includes the carrying out or validation of these tests by the notified body concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Sama kehtib ka tehasest, turult v&otilde;i ehituskohast v&otilde;etavate proovide auditeeritud katsetamiste kohta, kui kasutatavaks vastavuse t&otilde;endamise s&uuml;steemiks on toote sertifitseerimine ja selles n&otilde;utakse, et k&otilde;nealused katsed peab tegema v&otilde;i kinnitama asjaomane registreeritud asutus. </eesti>
<inglise> Test Records </inglise>
<eesti> Katseandmed </eesti>
<inglise> The manufacturer should establish and maintain records which provide evidence that the product has been tested. </inglise>
<eesti> Tootja peab sisse seadma ja s&auml;ilitama toodete katsetamist t&otilde;endava andmekogu. </eesti>
<inglise> These records should show clearly whether the product has satisfied the defined acceptance criteria. </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud andmekogu peab selgelt n&auml;itama, kas toode vastas etten&auml;htud n&otilde;uetekohasuse kriteeriumidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the product fails to satisfy the acceptance measures, the provisions for non-conforming products should apply. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui toode n&otilde;uetekohasuse kriteeriumidele ei vasta, kohaldatakse mittevastavate toodete suhtes kehtivaid s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise> 3.2.4. </inglise>
<eesti> 3.2.4. </eesti>
<inglise> Treatment of products which do not conform. </inglise>
<eesti> Mittevastavate toodete k&auml;sitlemine </eesti>
<inglise> If control or test results show that the product does not meet the requirements, for example if the statistical variation of test results exceeds the limits allowed by the technical specification, the necessary corrective action must immediately be taken. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui kontrolli- v&otilde;i katsetulemused n&auml;itavad, et toode ei vasta n&otilde;uetele, n&auml;iteks katsetulemuste statistiline erinevus &uuml;letab tehnilises kirjelduses lubatud piirid, tuleb kohe v&otilde;tta vajalikud parandusmeetmed. </eesti>
<inglise> Products or batches not conforming must be isolated and properly identified. </inglise>
<eesti> Mittevastavad tooted ja tootepartiid tuleb eraldada ning n&otilde;uetekohaselt m&auml;rgistada. </eesti>
